text:
Hi guys - I wondered if anyone could help point me in the right direction please? We are working on a web page which is listing out values from the HubDB - see screen shot attached.

At the moment the results are static but we would like to integrate Ajax filtering so that by changing the slider values at the top of the page the data is dynamically filtered.

Do you know whether this is possible within HubSpot and if so are there any examples out there which I can take a look at?

Many thanks,
Chris
Chris this is possible, and there is an API which you can use for this <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/hubdb/hubdb_overview>
I’m afraid I don’t really have good examples however
<@U7SL518D6> thanks for getting back to me and for the link provided - this is really useful. Chris
<@UEDR4M5KR> This is a get request. pretty strait forward if you ware familiar with ajax
